               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170416-155-person1169">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PRICE
               <interp inst="t18170416-155-person1169" type="surname" value="PRICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170416-155-person1169" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170416-155-person1169" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Bread-street, Cheapside. On the 1st of March, I was in Holborn, between four and five o'clock in the afternoon; when I came to <placeName id="t18170416-155-crimeloc811">Broad-street, St. Giles's</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170416-155-crimeloc811" type="placeName" value="Broad-street, St. Giles's"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170416-155-crimeloc811" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170416-155-off809 t18170416-155-crimeloc811"></join>, there was a crowd - I was passing through it; just before I got to Queen-street, I felt something touch my pocket, and I missed my handkerchief. The prisoner turned round, and asked me if I had lost any thing, and the officer secured him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170416-155-person1170">
                  JOHN 
                  LINES
               <interp inst="t18170416-155-person1170" type="surname" value="LINES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170416-155-person1170" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170416-155-person1170" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the prisoner, and six more men. I followed them down Oxford-road. The prisoner made a rush between the others, and took the handkerchief out of Mr. Price's pocket - I searched him, and took the handkerchief out of his hat.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
